==Romanian==

===Etymology===
Note:
Albanian ylber ` rainbow ' loanword from Romanian (*curcu-beu) curcubeu `rainbow' : Sardinian (*circu-voglia), circuvoglia, (*circu-vrongia) circuvrongia ` rainbow ', Sardinian Logudoresu arcu de chelu, (*arcu-baradu) arcubaradu, Sicilian (*arcu-bbalenu) arcubbalenu, Welsh bwa'r arch, Romagnolo (*arco-balèin) arcobalèin, Italian (*arco-baleno) arcobaleno. 
'Circu' means 'circle' in Sardinian, as 'cerc' (>Latin circus) means 'circle' in Romanian (circle >arc >rainbow). 
.
